Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
pinAnalysis(25.10)                                          pinAnalysis(25.10)

Name
       pinAnalysis  - Reports certain Quality of Results (QoR) metrics for pin
       assignment

Syntax
       pinAnalysis

       [-help]

       [-checkLegality]

       [-outFile <fileName>]

       [-noHtml]

       Reports certain Quality of Results (QoR) metrics  for  pin  assignment.
       The  pinAnalysis  command deletes the existing routes, reroutes the de-
       sign ensuring that the routes pass through partition pins, and  reports
       pin  assignment  QoR  metrics. You can run this command after assigning
       partition pins.

       Notes:

              * The pinAnalysis  command  creates  new  routes.  The  original
                routes are not retained.

              * The  pinAnalysis  command reroutes the design using  setRoute-
                Mode  -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin.  This  command  thus
                takes at least as much time as running Early Global Route.

              * In  addition  to  displaying the report on screen, the command
                also generates the report in  an  HTML  file  named  pinAnaly-
                sis.html.

              * This  command  is  not  supported  by Multi Level Hierarchical
                Flow. It displays a warning message when  used  for  a  design
                with  nested  partitions and generates results based on single
                level partitions.

Parameters
       -checkLegality
              Checks the legality of pin assignment  (similar  to  the  check-
              PinAssignmentcommand)  and  prints  a  summary report of the re-
              sults.

              The legality details for every partition are  available  through
              hyperlinks that are provided in the HTML report file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each pinAnalysis parameter. For a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command: man pinAnalysis

       -noHtml
              Specifies that HTML report file should not be created.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -outFile <fileName>
              In addition to displaying the report on screen, prints  the  re-
              port to the specified file.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following  command checks the legality of pin assignment, displays
       the QoR report for pin assignment on the screen, and  also  prints  the
       QoR report to a file named pinAnalysisMetricReport

       pinAnalysis -checkLegality -outFile pinAnalysisMetricReport

